trans-unit.source: A cast to a union type is a C extension not available in C++. It looks just like ordinary casts with the constraint that the type specified is a union type. You can specify the type either with the union keyword or with a typedef name that refers to a union. The result of a cast to a union is a temporary rvalue of the union type with a member whose type matches that of the operand initialized to the value of the operand. The effect of a cast to a union is similar to a compound literal except that it yields an rvalue like standard casts do. See Compound Literals.
trans-unit.target: Una conversión a un tipo de unión es una extensión de C no disponible en C ++. Se parece a las conversiones ordinarias con la restricción de que el tipo especificado es un tipo de unión. Puede especificar el tipo con la palabra clave union o con un nombre typedef que haga referencia a una unión. El resultado de una conversión a unión es un rvalue temporal del tipo union con un miembro cuyo tipo coincide con el del operando inicializado con el valor del operando. El efecto de una conversión a una unión es similar a un literal compuesto excepto que produce un valor r como lo hacen las conversiones estándar. Consulte Literales compuestos .

trans-unit.source: A compiler conforms to an ABI if it generates code that follows all of the specifications enumerated by that ABI. An application conforms to an ABI if it is built using tools that conform to that ABI and does not contain source code that specifically changes behavior specified by the ABI.

trans-unit.source: A compound literal looks like a cast of a brace-enclosed aggregate initializer list. trans-unit.source: A memory transaction commits all changes to memory in an atomic way, as visible to other threads. If the transaction fails it is rolled back and all side effects discarded.
trans-unit.target: Una transacción de memoria compromete todos los cambios en la memoria de una manera atómica,como es visible para otros hilos.Si la transacción falla,se devuelve y se descartan todos los efectos secundarios.

trans-unit.source: A nested function always has no linkage. Declaring one with extern or static is erroneous. If you need to declare the nested function before its definition, use auto (which is otherwise meaningless for function declarations).

trans-unit.source: A parameter to control whether to use function internal id in profile database lookup. If the value is 0, the compiler uses an id that is based on function assembler name and filename, which makes old profile data more tolerant to source changes such as function reordering etc.
